title: nethermind 1.13.4 does not sync from other nodes, or produce any blocks on Venidium network

body: @dceleda is it because of the switch in default sync mode to snap sync? Was it applied only to mainnet or to all the networks mistakenly?

@itsfridaythen Thanks for a such well described issue!

We've introduced an unexpected(at least for me) breaking change in 1.13.4:
In case you do not use your own configuration file, mainnet.cfg settings are used by default and since the update SnapSync is enabled by default for the mainnet configuration, which means it's enabled for your network too.

To fix it for now you can explicitly disable SnapSync by appending your environment settings with:

```
      NETHERMIND_SYNCCONFIG_SNAPSYNC: "false"
```

I'll post an update if we will be able to propose a different approach
@itsfridaythen does the proposed config change fixes your issue?

Just gave it a try and it fixes the issue.
Although explicit is better than implicit (so I will keep SnapSync set to false), will the currently default behavior regarding SnapSync be changing in a future release?

Agree. We should change that behavior.
https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/issues/4289
